Class Coordinator

    • Method Detail

      • buildOverlay

        public void buildOverlay​()
                  throws NoSuchAlgorithmException
        Builds the Chord overlay. The Coordinator generates nodesNumber strings of the form "IPaddress:port", where IP addressess are generated as four random integers x.y.w.z between 0 and 255 and port is a random integer between 0 and 65535. (The builder keeps track of generated strings and avoids duplicates.) Then, the string gets hashed and truncated to idSpaceBits bits and inserted into the ring, avoiding duplicates. In any case, the builder throws an exception if at any point it takes more than 500k iterations to build a single node. After creating the nodes, the builder proceeds to generate each node's finger table and to set each node's successor and predecessor.
        Throws:
        NoSuchAlgorithmException - If the current JVM doesn't support SHA-512.

      • createFingerTable

        private BigInteger[] createFingerTable​(BigInteger id)
        Creates the finger table for a particular ID. The built finger tables employ a trick to save space for the data structure: if for any x it holds fingertable[x] == fingertable[0] == successor(ID), then a null value is stored instead of the actual value. In this way, the algorithm that uses the finger table (Node's lookup method) has to substitute any null value with fingertable[0].
        Parameters:
        id - the ID of the node for which the finger table must be built
        Returns:
        an array of BigIntegers corresponding to the node's finger table
